<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910417-0012</DOCNO><DOCID>910417-0012.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Bally Manufacturing Corp.:   Preliminary Accords Reached   With Several Bank Lenders</HL><DATE>04/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   BLY BHT</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>CASINOS AND GAMBLING (CNO)ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)</IN><RE>ILLINOIS (IL)</RE><LP>   Bally Manufacturing Corp. said it reached preliminaryagreements with both the bank lenders of the parent companyand its health club unit on restructured credit facilities.   The debt-laden casino, health-club and manufacturingcompany, which is based in Chicago, has been negotiating withbank lenders and other creditors since last fall. It has alsomissed several interest payments on its debt securities.</LP><TEXT>   In its annual filing with the Securities and ExchangeCommission, Bally said that the agreements weren't formalcommitments and were subject to &quot;significant&quot; conditions. Butit said it obtained a $10 million &quot;demand bridge loan&quot; fromthe parent company's bank lenders in March and used theproceeds to purchase &quot;certain public debt securities.&quot;   Bally said in the filing that it signed letters of intentto sell certain of its products and services businesses. Itdidn't identify the businesses or the buyers.</TEXT></DOC>